{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_017i26RfCTPGBreCJujjgGrN","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have all the information I need. Let me compile it and write a comprehensive migration plan.\n\nCurrent state:\n- **Version**: v24.1.0 (CockroachDB CCL)\n- **Nodes**: 3 nodes (crdb-cluster-0, -1, -2), all running v24.1\n- **Deployment**: StatefulSet with 3 replicas, Parallel pod management\n- **Image**: cockroachdb/cockroach:v24.1.0\n- **Resources**: 1 CPU, 2Gi memory (requests = limits)\n- **Storage**: 10Gi PVC per node with standard StorageClass and read-write-once access\n- **TLS**: Enabled with certificates mounted from a secret, plus additional security flags for logging and memory management\n- **Update strategy**: RollingUpdate configured with partition control\n- **Cluster settings**: Custom secret key configured for the cluster\n\n, telemetry enabled, auto-merge queue disabled, and rebalance rate increased to 208 MiB/s (much higher than the default 8 MiB/s)\n- **Version**: Running CockroachDB 24.1\n- **Zone configurations**: Default ranges use 3 replicas with 4-hour garbage collection, system database uses 5 replicas, and the lease table has a much shorter 10-minute TTL while metadata ranges keep just 3-second retention\n- **Additional zone settings**: System and liveness ranges both use 5 replicas with standard TTLs, and there are specific replica and GC configurations for tables in the tenant_b database\n- **Services**: Two Kubernetes services expose the cluster (headless and ClusterIP)\n- **Next steps**: The cluster is on v24.1 from May 2024, so the next minor version would be v24.2 (released August 2024), followed by v24.3\n\nNow I'm planning out the migration strategy, which should include the current state, target version, pre-upgrade checks, the rolling upgrade process via StatefulSet image updates, post-upgrade verification, rollback procedures, and risk assessment. Rolling upgrades are key for CockroachDB since they allow the cluster to stay operational during the transition.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":654,"cache_read_input_tokens":34046,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":654},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"4ca65e78-0340-4831-9201-feff53cf9a12","uuid":"fd8a2d83-659c-4929-a421-354b3cdbdbe5","request_id":"req_011CcP43cCXSMeCyAjH7hLiv"}
