{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_017i26RfCTPGBreCJujjgGrN","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01YMky64RyP9WhYiDdDX4khy","name":"Bash","input":{"command":"cat > /tmp/plan.md << 'PLAN_EOF'\n# CockroachDB Minor-Version Upgrade Change Plan\n\n**Prepared:** 2026-06-24  \n**Review status:** PENDING — do not execute until approved  \n**Target window:** separate maintenance window, TBD  \n**Author:** automated cluster inspection\n\n---\n\n## 1. Current Cluster State (as-found, read-only inspection)\n\n### 1.1 Binary & Cluster Version\n\n| Field | Value |\n|---|---|\n| Binary version | v24.1.0 |\n| Active cluster version | 24.1 |\n| Build type | CCL (Commercial) |\n| Platform | linux amd64 |\n| Go version | go1.22.2 |\n| Build date | 2024-05-15 |\n\n### 1.2 Topology\n\n| Item | Value |\n|---|---|\n| Namespace | cockroachdb |\n| StatefulSet | crdb-cluster |\n| Replicas | 3 (crdb-cluster-0, crdb-cluster-1, crdb-cluster-2) |\n| Pod management policy | Parallel |\n| Update strategy | RollingUpdate (partition=0) |\n| All nodes live | Yes (all 3 at v24.1) |\n\n### 1.3 Container & Resource Configuration\n\n| Field | Value |\n|---|---|\n| Image | cockroachdb/cockroach:v24.1.0 |\n| Image pull policy | IfNotPresent |\n| CPU request/limit | 1 core |\n| Memory request/limit | 2 Gi |\n| PVC per node | 10 Gi (standard StorageClass, RWO) |\n| --cache | 25% |\n| --max-sql-memory | 25% |\n| --logtostderr | INFO |\n| TLS mode | Enabled (--certs-dir=/cockroach/cockroach-certs) |\n| Cert source | Secret cockroachdb-certs |\n| termination grace period | 60 s |\n\n### 1.4 Startup Join String\n\n```\ncrdb-cluster-0.crdb-cluster.cockroachdb.svc.cluster.local:26257\ncrdb-cluster-1.crdb-cluster.cockroachdb.svc.cluster.local:26257\ncrdb-cluster-2.crdb-cluster.cockroachdb.svc.cluster.local:26257\n```\n\n### 1.5 Services\n\n| Name | Type | Ports |\n|---|---|---|\n| crdb-cluster | ClusterIP (headless) | 26257/TCP, 8080/TCP |\n| crdb-cluster-public | ClusterIP (10.96.246.26) | 26257/TCP, 8080/TCP |\n\n### 1.6 Non-Default Cluster Settings\n\n```sql\nvariable                         value\n-------------------------------  ----------------------------------------\ncluster.secret                   0c41f502-0278-4983-b42d-f81b42a7b3d1\ndiagnostics.reporting.enabled    true\nkv.range_merge.queue.enabled     false\nkv.snapshot_rebalance.max_rate   208 MiB\nversion                          24.1\n```\n\n- **`kv.range_merge.queue.enabled = false`**: automatic range merge queue is disabled (tuning choice — prevents ranges from auto-merging).\n- **`kv.snapshot_rebalance.max_rate = 208 MiB`**: rebalance/upreplication snapshot bandwidth cap raised well above the CockroachDB default of 8 MiB/s.\n- **`diagnostics.reporting.enabled = true`**: telemetry reporting to Cockroach Labs is explicitly enabled.\n\n### 1.7 Zone Configurations\n\n| Target | num_replicas | gc.ttlseconds | Notes |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| RANGE default | 3 | 14400 (4 h) | Governs all user ranges not otherwise overridden |\n| DATABASE system | 5 | 14400 | System DB gets extra replicas for durability |\n| RANGE meta | 5 | 3600 (1 h) | Range metadata, 5 replicas |\n| RANGE system | 5 | 14400 | System ranges, 5 replicas |\n| RANGE liveness | 5 | 600 (10 min) | Node liveness, short GC TTL |\n| TABLE system.public.lease | — | 600 | Short GC TTL only |\n| TABLE system.public.replication_constraint_stats | — | 600 | Short GC TTL only |\n| TABLE system.public.replication_stats | — | 600 | Short GC TTL only |\n| TABLE system.public.statement_statistics | — | 3600 | |\n| TABLE system.public.transaction_statistics | — | 3600 | |\n| TABLE system.public.tenant_usage | — | 7200 (2 h) | |\n| TABLE system.public.span_stats_tenant_boundaries | — | 3600 | |\n| TABLE system.public.statement_activity | — | 3600 | |\n| TABLE system.public.transaction_activity | — | 3600 | |\n| TABLE defaultdb.tenant_b.table_c | 3 | 14400 | User table with explicit zone config |\n| TABLE defaultdb.tenant_b.table_d | 3 | 14400 | User table with explicit zone config |\n\n**Notable:** system ranges (meta, system, liveness, system DB) are pinned at 5 replicas even though the cluster only has 3 nodes. CockroachDB accepts this configuration — ranges will attempt to place 5 replicas but can only place 3 on a 3-node cluster; the under-replication is expected and flagged in the Admin UI.\n\n### 1.8 Databases\n\n| Database | Owner |\n|---|---|\n| defaultdb | root |\n| postgres | root |\n| system | node |\n\n---\n\n## 2. Target State\n\n### 2.1 Target Version\n\nUpgrade from **v24.1.0 → v24.2.x** (next minor release line).  \nRecommended: pin to the latest patch in the v24.2 series at execution time (e.g., v24.2.5 or later) to include all security and stability fixes.\n\nThe cluster version setting (`version`) will be finalized to `24.2` after all nodes are running the new binary.\n\n### 2.2 What Changes\n\n| Component | Before | After |\n|---|---|---|\n| StatefulSet image | cockroachdb/cockroach:v24.1.0 | cockroachdb/cockroach:v24.2.x |\n| Active cluster version (SQL) | 24.1 | 24.2 (set post-upgrade) |\n| Binary on each pod | v24.1.0 | v24.2.x |\n\n### 2.3 What Does NOT Change\n\nAll of the following are preserved as-found:\n\n- Replica count: 3 pods\n- All resource requests/limits (1 CPU, 2 Gi memory)\n- PVC sizes (10 Gi each)\n- All startup flags (--cache, --max-sql-memory, --logtostderr, --certs-dir, --join)\n- TLS configuration and certificate secret\n- All non-default cluster settings (`kv.range_merge.queue.enabled`, `kv.snapshot_rebalance.max_rate`, `diagnostics.reporting.enabled`)\n- All zone configurations for system and user tables\n- Service definitions\n- ServiceAccount (crdb-cluster-sa)\n\n---\n\n## 3. Pre-Upgrade Checklist\n\nComplete every item and record the outcome before entering the maintenance window.\n\n### 3.1 Cluster Health (run day-of, before starting)\n\n```bash\n# All nodes healthy and live\nkubectl -n cockroachdb exec crdb-cluster-0 -- \\\n  ./cockroach node status --certs-dir=/cockroach/cockroach-certs\n\n# No under-replicated or unavailable ranges\nkubectl -n cockroachdb exec crdb-cluster-0 -- \\\n  ./cockroach sql --certs-dir=/cockroach/cockroach-certs \\\n  -e \"SELECT * FROM crdb_internal.cluster_replication_status;\"\n\n# All pods Running and Ready\nkubectl -n cockroachdb get pods\n```\n\nExpected: 3/3 nodes live, 0 under-replicated ranges, all pods Ready.\n\n### 3.2 Backup\n\nTake a full cluster backup before starting.\n\n```bash\n# Example: backup to an object store (adjust URI to your target)\nkubectl -n cockroachdb exec crdb-cluster-0 -- \\\n  ./cockroach sql --certs-dir=/cockroach/cockroach-certs \\\n  -e \"BACKUP INTO 's3://your-bucket/crdb-pre-v24.2-upgrade/$(date +%Y%m%d)' \\\n      AS OF SYSTEM TIME '-10s';\"\n```\n\nConfirm the backup completes successfully before proceeding.\n\n### 3.3 Snapshot Current Configuration\n\n```bash\n# Save cluster settings to a file for rollback reference\nkubectl -n cockroachdb exec crdb-cluster-0 -- \\\n  ./cockroach sql --certs-dir=/cockroach/cockroach-certs \\\n  -e \"SELECT variable, value FROM crdb_internal.cluster_settings WHERE value != default_value;\" \\\n  > crdb-settings-snapshot-$(date +%Y%m%d).txt\n\n# Save zone configs\nkubectl -n cockroachdb exec crdb-cluster-0 -- \\\n  ./cockroach sql --certs-dir=/cockroach/cockroach-certs \\\n  -e \"SELECT target, raw_config_sql FROM crdb_internal.zones;\" \\\n  >> crdb-settings-snapshot-$(date +%Y%m%d).txt\n\n# Save StatefulSet spec\nkubectl -n cockroachdb get statefulset crdb-cluster -o yaml \\\n  > crdb-statefulset-snapshot-$(date +%Y%m%d).yaml\n```\n\n### 3.4 Verify Target Image Availability\n\n```bash\ndocker pull cockroachdb/cockroach:v24.2.x   # replace x with actual patch\n# OR verify the image is accessible from the cluster nodes\n```\n\n### 3.5 Review v24.2 Release Notes\n\nCheck https://www.cockroachlabs.com/docs/releases/v24.2 for:\n- Any deprecated settings used by this cluster (`kv.range_merge.queue.enabled`, `kv.snapshot_rebalance.max_rate`)\n- SQL compatibility changes affecting `defaultdb.tenant_b.table_c` / `table_d`\n- Any required pre-upgrade SQL migrations noted in the release notes\n\n---\n\n## 4. Upgrade Procedure\n\nCockroachDB supports **rolling upgrades** — nodes are replaced one at a time while the cluster remains available. The cluster operates in a mixed-version state (24.1 + 24.2) temporarily; this is fully supported.\n\n### 4.1 Update the StatefulSet Image\n\n```bash\nkubectl -n cockroachdb set image statefulset/crdb-cluster \\\n  db=cockroachdb/cockroach:v24.2.x\n```\n\nThis triggers a RollingUpdate. Because `podManagementPolicy: Parallel` is set, Kubernetes will restart pods in order but may start multiple rollouts simultaneously. Watch the rollout:\n\n```bash\nkubectl -n cockroachdb rollout status statefulset/crdb-cluster --timeout=10m\n```\n\n### 4.2 Monitor Each Node During Rollout\n\nFor each pod that restarts (crdb-cluster-2 → crdb-cluster-1 → crdb-cluster-0 typical order):\n\n```bash\n# Confirm pod is running the new binary\nkubectl -n cockroachdb exec crdb-cluster-<N> -- \\\n  ./cockroach version --certs-dir=/cockroach/cockroach-certs\n\n# Check node status from any surviving node\nkubectl -n cockroachdb exec crdb-cluster-0 -- \\\n  ./cockroach node status --certs-dir=/cockroach/cockroach-certs\n```\n\nWait for each node to show as live before the next pod restarts. With `terminationGracePeriodSeconds: 60`, the cluster has time to drain leases.\n\n### 4.3 Verify All Nodes Are on v24.2\n\n```bash\nkubectl -n cockroachdb exec crdb-cluster-0 -- \\\n  ./cockroach node status --certs-dir=/cockroach/cockroach-certs\n# All 3 nodes should show version 24.2\n```\n\n### 4.4 Finalize the Cluster Version\n\nOnce **all** nodes are running v24.2 binaries, promote the internal cluster version. This is a one-way operation — it enables v24.2-only features and cannot be rolled back afterward.\n\n```bash\nkubectl -n cockroachdb exec crdb-cluster-0 -- \\\n  ./cockroach sql --certs-dir=/cockroach/cockroach-certs \\\n  -e \"SET CLUSTER SETTING version = '24.2';\"\n```\n\nVerify:\n\n```bash\nkubectl -n cockroachdb exec crdb-cluster-0 -- \\\n  ./cockroach sql --certs-dir=/cockroach/cockroach-certs \\\n  -e \"SHOW CLUSTER SETTING version;\"\n```\n\nExpected output: `24.2`\n\n---\n\n## 5. Post-Upgrade Verification\n\nRun all checks within 30 minutes of completing the upgrade.\n\n```bash\n# 1. All 3 nodes live and decommissioned count = 0\nkubectl -n cockroachdb exec crdb-cluster-0 -- \\\n  ./cockroach node status --certs-dir=/cockroach/cockroach-certs\n\n# 2. No under-replicated or unavailable ranges\nkubectl -n cockroachdb exec crdb-cluster-0 -- \\\n  ./cockroach sql --certs-dir=/cockroach/cockroach-certs \\\n  -e \"SELECT * FROM crdb_internal.cluster_replication_status;\"\n\n# 3. Non-default cluster settings preserved\nkubectl -n cockroachdb exec crdb-cluster-0 -- \\\n  ./cockroach sql --certs-dir=/cockroach/cockroach-certs \\\n  -e \"SELECT variable, value FROM crdb_internal.cluster_settings WHERE value != default_value;\"\n\n# Expected rows:\n#   kv.range_merge.queue.enabled   = false\n#   kv.snapshot_rebalance.max_rate = 208 MiB\n#   diagnostics.reporting.enabled  = true\n#   version                        = 24.2\n\n# 4. Zone configs preserved — spot-check the custom user tables\nkubectl -n cockroachdb exec crdb-cluster-0 -- \\\n  ./cockroach sql --certs-dir=/cockroach/cockroach-certs \\\n  -e \"SELECT target, raw_config_sql FROM crdb_internal.zones WHERE target LIKE '%tenant_b%';\"\n\n# 5. Basic SQL connectivity\nkubectl -n cockroachdb exec crdb-cluster-0 -- \\\n  ./cockroach sql --certs-dir=/cockroach/cockroach-certs \\\n  -e \"SELECT 1;\"\n\n# 6. Check for any new decommissioned or suspect nodes\nkubectl -n cockroachdb exec crdb-cluster-0 -- \\\n  ./cockroach sql --certs-dir=/cockroach/cockroach-certs \\\n  -e \"SELECT node_id, is_live FROM crdb_internal.gossip_liveness;\"\n```\n\n---\n\n## 6. Rollback Plan\n\n**Window for rollback:** Before finalizing the cluster version (Step 4.4). Once `SET CLUSTER SETTING version = '24.2'` is executed, rollback to v24.1 is not supported by CockroachDB.\n\n### If rollback is needed before version finalization:\n\n```bash\n# Revert the StatefulSet image to v24.1.0\nkubectl -n cockroachdb set image statefulset/crdb-cluster \\\n  db=cockroachdb/cockroach:v24.1.0\n\n# Wait for rollout\nkubectl -n cockroachdb rollout status statefulset/crdb-cluster --timeout=10m\n\n# Confirm all nodes back on v24.1\nkubectl -n cockroachdb exec crdb-cluster-0 -- \\\n  ./cockroach node status --certs-dir=/cockroach/cockroach-certs\n```\n\nThe cluster version setting will still read `24.1` (it was never changed), so no SQL revert is needed.\n\n### If rollback is needed after version finalization:\n\nFull restore from the pre-upgrade backup is required. This involves:\n1. Provisioning a fresh v24.1.0 cluster\n2. Restoring the backup taken in Step 3.2\n3. Reconfiguring zone configs and cluster settings from the snapshots taken in Step 3.3\n\nThis is an extended recovery operation — do not finalize the cluster version until the upgrade is confirmed stable.\n\n---\n\n## 7. Risk Assessment\n\n| Risk | Likelihood | Impact | Mitigation |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| Pod restart fails / image pull error | Low | Medium — one node down temporarily, cluster remains available | Pre-pull image (Step 3.4); 2 remaining nodes maintain quorum |\n| Mixed-version state causes query errors | Very Low | Low — CRDB is designed for this | Monitor app error rates during rollout; rollback image if errors spike |\n| `kv.range_merge.queue.enabled` deprecated in v24.2 | Low | Low — will log a warning, setting will be ignored or removed | Review v24.2 release notes (Step 3.5) |\n| `kv.snapshot_rebalance.max_rate` API change | Low | Low | Same review |\n| Cluster version finalization fails | Very Low | Low — retry the SET command | Cluster stays on 24.1 behavior until finalized |\n| Data loss | Very Low | High | Full backup required before starting (Step 3.2) |\n| Under-replication during rollout | Expected | Low — transient; 5-replica zones on a 3-node cluster already report under-replicated | Monitor in Admin UI; wait for rebalancing before finalizing version |\n\n---\n\n## 8. Estimated Downtime\n\n**Expected downtime for client connections: zero** (rolling upgrade with quorum maintained throughout).\n\nEach pod restart takes approximately 60–120 seconds (60 s grace period + startup). With 3 pods:\n- Total rollout time: ~5–10 minutes\n\nThe cluster remains fully available to reads and writes throughout. Individual SQL connections routed through the restarting pod may see brief disconnects; clients should use the `crdb-cluster-public` ClusterIP service and implement reconnect logic.\n\n---\n\n## 9. Change Summary (what this plan authorizes)\n\n| Action | Authorized |\n|---|---|\n| Update StatefulSet image from v24.1.0 → v24.2.x | YES |\n| Finalize cluster version to 24.2 after all nodes updated | YES |\n| Change any cluster settings | NO |\n| Change any zone configurations | NO |\n| Change replica counts | NO |\n| Change resource limits | NO |\n| Change TLS configuration | NO |\n| Change any service or network configuration | NO |\n\nThis plan authorizes **only** the image update and version finalization. All other configuration is preserved exactly as-found.\n\n---\n\n*End of change plan — awaiting peer review and approval.*\nPLAN_EOF\necho \"Plan written, $(wc -l < /tmp/plan.md) lines\"","description":"Write migration plan to temp file"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":654,"cache_read_input_tokens":34046,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":654},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_u